152. non illic] Erasmus had diverged to Bel-gen (Ep. 301). His visits there and at Louvain must have been very brief; cf. ll. 7, 8 supra.

156. Catonem] Cf. Ep. 298.

161. Meynardo] Meyn. Mann († 1526) of Wormer, S. of Alcmar 3 36th Abbot of Egmond, W. of Alcmar. He rebuilt the Abbey after its destruction in a fire which caused the death of his prede- cessor, 30 Oct. 1509; see van Heussen, Balavia sacra, 1714, ii. 430. Dorp was indebted to him for a benefice (see the preface to his Oratio cle laudibus discipli- narum, Louvain, Th. Martens, 14 Oct. 1513, dedicated to Manu) 3 and also

addressed to him a letter which was printed in the first edition of Adrian of Utrecht's monumenta, Louvain, Th. Martens, March 1515, but not in later editions. Corn. Gerard (Ep. 17 introd.) praises him at length in Batauia, 1586, p. 17, for his antiquarian interests; and John Murmell of Roermond dedi- cated to him his Charoleia, Louvain, Th. Mal-tens, 3. cz„ with a preface dated 24 April 1515.

Erasmus did not act upon the sugges- tion made here; but mentions Manu with praise in dedicating Eucherius to Alard of Amsterdam (Ep. 433), who was Mann's kinsman.
